<%- include('../partials/page-hero', { heroTitle: 'Terms & Conditions', heroTagline: 'Policies & Guidelines', heroText: 'The terms governing your use of the GDCU website, applications, and student services.' }) %>

<section class="py-16 lg:py-20 bg-surface-bright">
  <div class="max-w-container-max mx-auto px-margin-mobile lg:px-margin-desktop">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-gdcu">
      <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-sm mb-8"><em>Last updated: July 2026</em></p>

      <h3>1. Use of Website</h3>
      <p>By accessing and using the Global Diaspora Christian University (GDCU) website, you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, you should not use our website or services.</p>
      <p>We reserve the right to update these terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page and, where appropriate, notified to registered users.</p>

      <h3>2. Applications</h3>
      <p>All applications for admission to GDCU are subject to the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Applicants must provide accurate, complete, and truthful information.</li>
        <li>GDCU reserves the right to verify the information provided and to request supporting documentation.</li>
        <li>Submission of an application does not guarantee admission.</li>
        <li>GDCU may reject an application or withdraw an offer if information is found to be false or misleading.</li>
        <li>Application fees, where applicable, are non-refundable unless specified otherwise.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Admissions</h3>
      <p>Admission decisions are made by the GDCU Admissions Committee and are based on academic qualifications, personal statements, references, and other relevant criteria. All decisions are final and at the discretion of the university.</p>
      <p>Offers of admission may be conditional or unconditional. Conditional offers require the applicant to meet specified requirements by a stated deadline.</p>

      <h3>4. Fees and Payments</h3>
      <p>Tuition fees and other charges are published on our website and in offer letters. By accepting an offer of admission, you agree to pay the applicable fees in accordance with the payment schedule.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Fees are quoted in Great British Pounds (GBP) unless otherwise stated.</li>
        <li>Payment plans may be available subject to approval by the Finance Office.</li>
        <li>Late or non-payment may result in suspension of access to courses and services.</li>
        <li>Refund policies are outlined in the Student Handbook and may vary by programme.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>5. Course Access</h3>
      <p>Upon enrolment and payment of applicable fees, students are granted access to their courses, learning materials, and student services through the GDCU online portal. Access is personal and non-transferable.</p>
      <p>GDCU reserves the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any course or programme, provided that reasonable alternatives or refunds are offered to affected students.</p>

      <h3>6. Student Responsibilities</h3>
      <p>As a GDCU student, you agree to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Engage with your studies in a timely and responsible manner</li>
        <li>Submit your own work and adhere to academic integrity policies</li>
        <li>Treat fellow students, faculty, and staff with respect and dignity</li>
        <li>Comply with the Student Handbook and all university policies</li>
        <li>Maintain the confidentiality of your login credentials</li>
        <li>Notify the university of any changes to your contact information</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>7. Intellectual Property</h3>
      <p>All course materials, content, and resources provided by GDCU are protected by copyright and other intellectual property laws. Students may access and use these materials for their personal educational purposes only.</p>
      <p>Reproduction, distribution, or commercial use of GDCU materials without written permission is strictly prohibited.</p>

      <h3>8. Limitation of Liability</h3>
      <p>GDCU provides its website and services on an "as is" and "as available" basis. To the fullest extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, express or implied, regarding the operation of our website and the provision of our services.</p>
      <p>GDCU shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of our website or services.</p>

      <h3>9. Changes to Terms</h3>
      <p>GDCU reserves the right to amend these Terms and Conditions at any time. Registered students will be notified of material changes via email or through the student portal. Continued use of our services after such changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.</p>

      <h3>10. Contact Details</h3>
      <p>If you have any questions about these Terms and Conditions, please contact us:</p>
      <p>
        <strong>Global Diaspora Christian University</strong><br>
        <%= siteCompany.addressLine1 %><br>
        <%= siteCompany.addressLine2 %><br>
        Florida LLC No. <span class="font-mono"><%= siteCompany.companyNumber %></span><br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:<%= siteCompany.email %>" class="text-secondary font-bold"><%= siteCompany.email %></a><br>
        Website: <a href="https://gdcu.edu" class="text-secondary font-bold">gdcu.edu</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
